physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Enlarged, multilocular ovaries measuring 14 cm in length; moderate amount of ascitic fluid (approximately 1 liter); levels of inhibin B markedly and inappropriately elevated.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: The ovaries remained enlarged throughout the pregnancy.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Estradiol level was 3510 ng/liter; inhibin B level was 401 ng/liter; follicle-stimulating hormone level was 0.025 U/liter; total testosterone level was 2 µg/liter; free testosterone was normal.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Estradiol stabilized within normal range during second trimester and increased further during third trimester.

Estradiol level was 13870 ng/liter; follicle-stimulating hormone level was 0.080 U/liter; total testosterone level was 1.6 µg/liter; free testosterone was normal.
